---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How St. John Biocare collects, uses, and protects your personal and health information under the Data Privacy Act of 2012 (RA 10173)."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:720px">
      <h1 id="top">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">Your trust matters, and your health information is private. This policy explains what
      we collect, why, how we protect it, and the rights you have — in line with the
      <strong>Data Privacy Act of 2012 (Republic Act No.&nbsp;10173)</strong>.</p>

      <p class="muted"><strong>Last updated:</strong> <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer]</mark>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Effective:</strong> <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer]</mark></p>

      <div class="notice">This policy is being finalised with our Data Protection Officer. If anything here is
      unclear, please contact us — we're happy to explain how your information is handled.</div>

      <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
      <nav class="toc" aria-label="On this page">
        <p class="toc__title">On this page</p>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#who-we-are">Who we are</a></li>
          <li><a href="#what-we-collect">The information we collect</a></li>
          <li><a href="#sensitive-data">Sensitive personal information (your health data)</a></li>
          <li><a href="#why-and-basis">Why we collect it, and our legal basis</a></li>
          <li><a href="#consent">Consent, and how to withdraw it</a></li>
          <li><a href="#sharing">Who we share it with</a></li>
          <li><a href="#cookies">Cookies and third-party services</a></li>
          <li><a href="#retention">How long we keep it</a></li>
          <li><a href="#security">How we protect it</a></li>
          <li><a href="#your-rights">Your rights under the Data Privacy Act</a></li>
          <li><a href="#children">Children's information</a></li>
          <li><a href="#changes">Changes to this policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#dpo">How to reach our Data Protection Officer</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <!-- 4 -->
      <h2 id="who-we-are">Who we are</h2>
      <p>St. John Biocare &amp; Dialysis Center Foundation, Inc. ("St. John Biocare," "we," "us") is the
      <strong>personal information controller</strong> responsible for the information collected through
      this website. Our administrative office is at #10 CK Building, South A Street corner Alejandro Roces
      Avenue, Barangay Paligsahan, Quezon City 1103.</p>
      <p>Our network includes centers operated under St. John Biocare, Core Renal Center, and the
      St. Josef Renal Care Foundation. Where you inquire about a specific center, your information is handled
      by that center's team. <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: the relationship between
      the three foundations for data-sharing purposes — same controller, affiliated controllers, or separate.]</mark></p>

      <!-- 5 -->
      <h2 id="what-we-collect">The information we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what you choose to give us through the forms on this site. Depending on the form,
      this may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>your <strong>name</strong> and <strong>contact details</strong> (mobile number and/or email);</li>
        <li>the <strong>center</strong> you're asking about and whether you're a <strong>new or transferring
        patient</strong>;</li>
        <li>whether you are a <strong>PhilHealth member</strong>;</li>
        <li>for job and training applicants: your <strong>PRC license number</strong>, <strong>résumé</strong>,
        and <strong>credentials</strong>;</li>
        <li>any <strong>files you upload</strong> (see the next section); and</li>
        <li>the <strong>message</strong> you write to us.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We also receive limited technical information automatically when you visit — see
      <a href="#cookies">Cookies and third-party services</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>What we do <em>not</em> do:</strong> the "personalised invitation letter" tool on our Training
      page creates your letter <strong>entirely on your own device</strong>. The name and address you type there
      are <strong>never sent to us or to anyone else.</strong></p>

      <!-- 6 -->
      <h2 id="sensitive-data">Sensitive personal information (your health data)</h2>
      <p>Some of our forms let you attach documents so we can help you faster — for example
      <strong>laboratory results, a doctor's referral, your PhilHealth Member Data Record (MDR)</strong>, or,
      for training applicants, a <strong>Hepatitis profile</strong> and <strong>vaccination records.</strong></p>
      <p>Under the Data Privacy Act, health information is <strong>sensitive personal information</strong> and
      receives stronger protection. We ask for it only when it helps us respond to you, we handle it with extra
      care, and <strong>you are never required to upload it to reach us</strong> — you may simply message or call,
      and bring your documents in person instead.</p>

      <!-- 7 -->
      <h2 id="why-and-basis">Why we collect it, and our legal basis</h2>
      <p>We use your information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>reply to your inquiry and answer your questions;</li>
        <li>arrange appointments and coordinate your dialysis care or transfer of care;</li>
        <li>process training and job applications; and</li>
        <li>keep the records we are required to keep as a healthcare provider.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Our legal bases under the Data Privacy Act include your <strong>consent</strong> (which you give when
      you tick the consent box and submit a form), the <strong>performance of services you request</strong>, and
      our <strong>compliance with legal and regulatory obligations</strong> as a DOH-regulated provider. We
      <strong>do not sell your information</strong>, and we <strong>do not use it for advertising.</strong>
      <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: the legal bases above, plus any others that apply —
      e.g. legitimate interest or medical-treatment provisions.]</mark></p>

      <!-- 8 -->
      <h2 id="consent">Consent, and how to withdraw it</h2>
      <p>When you submit a form, you confirm that you agree to our handling your information for the purpose you
      contacted us about. You may <strong>withdraw your consent</strong> at any time by contacting our Data
      Protection Officer (below). Withdrawing consent won't affect processing already done, and in some cases we
      may need to keep certain records to meet legal requirements.</p>

      <!-- 9 -->
      <h2 id="sharing">Who we share it with</h2>
      <p>We keep your information within St. John Biocare and share it only as needed to help you:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Our staff</strong> — only those who need it to respond to you or provide care.</li>
        <li><strong>Form delivery (Web3Forms).</strong> Our website forms are delivered through
        <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web3Forms</a>, a form-processing
        service, which passes your submission to the correct center's inbox.
        <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: a data-processing agreement with Web3Forms.]</mark></li>
        <li><strong>Hospitals and partners</strong>, only where necessary to arrange admission, emergency transfer,
        or specialist care you've asked for.</li>
        <li><strong>Authorities</strong>, only when required by law.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We <strong>do not sell or rent</strong> your information to anyone.
      <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: some center inboxes currently receive submissions in
      third-party webmail (Gmail/Yahoo). Either disclose that mail is handled by those providers under their own
      privacy terms, or migrate to managed email before launch.]</mark></p>

      <!-- 10 -->
      <h2 id="cookies">Cookies and third-party services</h2>
      <p>This website does <strong>not</strong> use advertising cookies and does <strong>not</strong> run analytics
      or tracking tools — we don't build a profile of you.</p>
      <p>A few features load content from other companies, which means those companies may receive your device's
      IP address:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Maps</strong> on our center pages are embedded from <strong>Google Maps</strong>;</li>
        <li><strong>Fonts</strong> are loaded from <strong>Google Fonts</strong>;</li>
        <li>the site is <strong>hosted on GitHub Pages</strong>, which keeps standard server logs for security.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These providers process that limited technical data under their own privacy policies.
      <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: whether to self-host fonts and/or make maps
      "click-to-load" to minimise third-party contact, and whether a cookie/consent banner is warranted
      (currently no first-party cookies are set).]</mark></p>

      <!-- 11 -->
      <h2 id="retention">How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>We keep your information only as long as needed for the purpose you shared it, and to meet our legal and
      record-keeping obligations as a healthcare provider, after which it is securely deleted or anonymised.</p>
      <p><mark>[Required — to be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: the actual retention periods for
      (a)&nbsp;website inquiries that don't become patients, (b)&nbsp;patient records, and (c)&nbsp;job/training
      applications that aren't successful. No figures are published here until confirmed.]</mark></p>

      <!-- 12 -->
      <h2 id="security">How we protect it</h2>
      <p>We limit access to staff who genuinely need it, keep physical and digital records secure, and train our
      people on confidentiality. No system is perfectly secure, but we take reasonable and appropriate
      organisational, physical, and technical measures to protect your information, as required by the Data Privacy
      Act. <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: alignment with the organisation's actual security
      policy and breach-notification procedure.]</mark></p>

      <!-- 13 -->
      <h2 id="your-rights">Your rights under the Data Privacy Act</h2>
      <p>As a data subject, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>be informed</strong> about how your information is used;</li>
        <li><strong>access</strong> the information we hold about you;</li>
        <li><strong>correct</strong> anything inaccurate;</li>
        <li><strong>object</strong> to or <strong>withdraw consent</strong> for certain processing;</li>
        <li>request <strong>deletion or blocking</strong> where appropriate;</li>
        <li><strong>data portability</strong> where applicable; and</li>
        <li><strong>complain</strong> to the National Privacy Commission if you believe your rights were violated.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these, contact our Data Protection Officer below and we'll guide you through it.</p>

      <!-- 14 -->
      <h2 id="children">Children's information</h2>
      <p>Our services and forms are intended for adults. Where care involves a minor, we rely on a parent's or
      guardian's involvement and consent. <mark>[To be confirmed by our Data Protection Officer: handling of minors'
      data, since some dialysis patients may be minors.]</mark></p>

      <!-- 15 -->
      <h2 id="changes">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top shows when it last changed,
      and material changes will be posted on this page.</p>

      <!-- 16 -->
      <h2 id="dpo">How to reach our Data Protection Officer</h2>
      <p>If you have questions, requests, or concerns about your information, please contact:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Data Protection Officer:</strong> William Gregory M. Rivero, MD <span class="muted">(interim)</span></li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@stjohnbiocare.com">hello@stjohnbiocare.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> +63 (2) 8375 1575</li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> #10 CK Building, South A Street corner Alejandro Roces Avenue, Barangay
        Paligsahan, Quezon City 1103</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You may also contact the <strong>National Privacy Commission</strong>
      (<a href="https://privacy.gov.ph" target="_blank" rel="noopener">privacy.gov.ph</a>) if your concern is
      unresolved.</p>

      <p><a href="#top" class="toc__back">↑ Back to top</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

